ned. Each piece provides a critical overview of the most significant films in relation to their industrial and social contexts. European Film Noir is an important contribution to the study of European cinema that will have a broad appeal to undergraduates, cinéastes, film teachers and researchers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFilm noirzEuropexHistory and criticism. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican film noir.  aBritish film noir.  aBritish neo-noir.  aEuropean cinemas.  aFrench polar.  aGerman neo-noir.  aItalian film noir.  aSpanish film noir.  aSpanish neo-noir.  afilmography.  anational cinema.1 aBergfelder, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooke, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavies, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurphy, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPowrie, Phil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpicer, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpicer, Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStone, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVincendeau, Ginette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWood, Mary P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614136140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141361423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141361/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester Univ